Data Stream Schedule in Data Cloud

Data streams can operate on different refresh schedules. To see the refresh history of a data stream, access the data stream's record page and click Refresh History.

Initiate a manual refresh of the data stream by clicking Refresh Now in the data stream's record page.

B2C Commerce
When you create a B2C Commerce data stream using the Order Bundle, Data Cloud loads 30 days of historical data. After you deploy the data stream, Data Cloud pulls new data based on this schedule.

DATA STREAM NAME	DATA TYPE	REFRESH MODE	REFRESH SCHEDULE

BundleProduct	Other	Full Refresh	Daily
GoodsProduct	Other	Full Refresh	Daily
MasterProduct	Other	Full Refresh	Daily
ProductCatalog	Other	Full Refresh	Daily
ProductCategory	Other	Full Refresh	Daily
ProductCategoryProduct	Other	Full Refresh	Daily
ProductOption	Other	Full Refresh	Daily
ProductOptionValue	Other	Full Refresh	Daily
ProductProductOption	Other	Full Refresh	Daily
SalesOrder	Engagement	Upsert	Hourly
SalesOrderCustomer	Profile	Full Refresh	Hourly

Cloud Storage
Data streams that use cloud storage sources such as AWS S3 or Google Cloud Storage (GCS) are refreshed on a pre-defined schedule, or manually through the data stream record home.

Ingestion API
The Ingestion API provides a RESTful interface that supports both streaming and bulk interaction patterns for programmatically loading data into Data Cloud. With Bulk Ingest API you can pull data at scheduled intervals, while with Stream Processing, data is processed continuously with minimal latency.

TYPE	SCHEDULE	DETAILS

Full	Every other week
Incremental	Every 10 minutes

Salesforce CRM
The Salesforce CRM connector conducts full and incremental refreshes on a set schedule, requiring no action from you.

Refresh times vary. Formulas are refreshed during a full or incremental refresh and are recalculated if a record has changed.

Batch and stream processing handle data differently. Batch processing processes the data at once at scheduled intervals. Stream processing, the default, continuously processes data with minimal latency.

The streaming process checks if a full refresh is required. The first instance of a full refresh always uses batch processing.

To allow streaming, permissions must be set and validation checks must be met.
title: Data Stream Scheduling in Salesforce Data Cloud
